    <article class="app-detail">
      <h1 class="app-detail-title">Support</h1>
      <p class="app-detail-tagline">We're here to help with Orbit</p>

      <div class="app-detail-content">
        <section class="app-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Contact Us</h2>
          <p class="app-detail-description">Having trouble with Orbit? Found a bug? Have a feature request? We'd love to hear from you.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="app-section">
          <a href="mailto:support@cosmique.io?subject=Orbit%20support" class="app-link">
            Email support@cosmique.io
          </a>
        </section>

        <section class="app-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">When contacting us</h2>
          <p class="app-detail-description">Please include:</p>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>A description of the issue or your feedback</li>
            <li>Your operating system and version (macOS, Linux, Windows)</li>
            <li>Your Orbit version number</li>
            <li>Whether you're running natively or with Docker</li>
            <li>Relevant log output (if applicable)</li>
            <li>Steps to reproduce the issue (if applicable)</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="app-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Documentation</h2>
          <p class="app-detail-description">For setup guides, configuration options, and API documentation, visit the official documentation.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="app-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Common Issues</h2>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><strong>Library not scanning</strong> — Check that the music directory path in your config file is correct and accessible.</li>
            <li><strong>Metadata not matching</strong> — Ensure your files have basic tags. Orbit uses these for initial matching against MusicBrainz.</li>
            <li><strong>DSD files not playing</strong> — Verify your playback device supports native DSD or enable transcoding in settings.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
